CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 9, 1941, pg. 3 reads: "James Weldon Johnson Camp Model Project - Above are scenes from Camp James Weldon Johnson, situated on Raccoon Creek in foothills of the beautiful Allegehney [Allegheny] mountains just 34 miles from Pittsburg. Some of the children who enjoyed the facilities of the spacious grounds during the past two weeks are pictured...Another scene in the dining hall as campers, counsellors and visitors enjoy an evening meal at Camp Johnson.  The happy lot of youngsters showed a gain of weight after several days at the camp..."
TitMainTitle: Girls, and boys, including one wearing sleeveless shirt, carrying tray, eating at wooden tables and benches in dining hall at Camp Weldon Johnson, Beaver County, Pennsylvania
